
1. Class Attributes

A class attribute is a variable that is shared by all objects of the class.

# Syntax
class Student:
    school = "ABC School"   # class attribute

s1 = Student()
s2 = Student()

print(s1.school)
print(s2.school)

~ Key Points
Defined inside class, outside methods
Same value for all objects
Stored only once



| Feature | Class Attribute       | Instance Attribute        |
| ------- | --------------------- | ------------------------- |
| Defined | Inside class          | Inside constructor/method |
| Keyword | No `self`             | Uses `self`               |
| Sharing | Shared by all objects | Unique per object         |
| Memory  | One copy              | Multiple copies           |
| Example | `school`              | `name`                    |
